Bluetongue, France
------------------
Information received on 11 Mar 2016 from Dr Loic Evain, Directeur General adjoint, CVO, Direction generale de l'alimentation, Ministere de l'Agriculture, de l'Agroalimentaire et de la Foret, Paris, France

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 26
Date of start of the event: 21 Aug 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 11 Sep 2015
Report date: 11 Mar 2016
Date submitted to OIE: 11 Mar 2016
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2010
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease [see commentary]
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 8
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 8
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2268 / 19 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, in percentages)
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.84 / 0.00 / 0.00 / 0.00

Affected population [in reference to all 8 new outbreaks]: Samples taken in the framework of the analytical surveillance [see comment to item 2]

